race.comment: CHESTIME (3) backs up five days after making a late challenge to get up for second in a comparable race to this at Scone. Ran well at her only appearance at Armidale four runs back. This looks an ideal race for her. AGE OF AQUARIUS (8) won here first-up then unsurprisingly didn't follow that up at Scone last time - his second-up form is not flattering. Placed three from three at this trip so watch for a much better run this time. FAST DA (4) has turned things around at his last two runs, the latest effort a handy third over 1200m at Inverell after travelling up on the speed. Worth an each-way ticket. Forget the last run of NEED A MIRACLE (5) in an unsuitable contest. Comes under notice based on a 0.6 length third over 1300m here two back. CHARLIE BALI (7) failed here last start but will appreciate a return to firmer footing this afternoon.
